<li id="cite_note-36"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Škend_Gumānīg_Wizār#cite_ref-36">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The author further develops the theme of the complete separation of good and evil, i.e., of Ohrmazd and Ahriman. He employs various philosophical analyses, including "the impossibility of any existent thing being infinite, the nature of infinity, the relationship between epistemology, essence, and quality, and the immutability of substance." Seyyed Hossein Nasr and Mehdi Aminrazavi at 5.</span>
